{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "T-ELF allows us to extract highly specific features from the data.",
    "This method identifies latent topics within the corpus, grouping documents into clusters based on shared themes.",
    "To avoid over/under-fitting, automatic model determination is used where the final cluster counts are determined by achieving the highest silhouette scores above a predetermined threshold using the Binary Bleed method [47].",
    "This method employs a binary search strategy across k values, selectively skipping those k values that do not surpass the silhouette threshold.",
    "The search criterion for an optimal k is defined as k optimal = max {k ∈ {1, 2,..., K}: S(f (k)) > T }, where S(f (k)) denotes the silhouette score of the k-th configuration and T the threshold."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
